import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About">
  <section class="page-head"><div class="shell"><p class="eyebrow">postgres@hacking:~$ man postgres-hacking</p><h1>A public workshop for hacking Postgres.</h1><p class="lede">We pick real problems, inspect the code, prototype fixes, test the ugly edges, and push useful work toward -hackers and CommitFest.</p><div class="actions"><a class="button primary" href="https://t.me/postgres_hacking">[join telegram]</a><a class="button" href="https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLH8y1BNPAKjKDdJA7sDmFWUkbbYux3TRz">[watch playlist]</a></div></div></section>
  <section class="section"><div class="shell split"><div><h2>Why “Postgres Hacking”?</h2><p class="lede">It works as the community and site name. “Hacking Postgres” remains the session-series title used by PostgresTV. Both point to the same work.</p><h2 style="margin-top:2.2rem">How to contribute</h2><ol class="detail-list"><li>Join the Telegram group and pick a work line.</li><li>Read the patch, thread, and current blockers before writing code.</li><li>Reproduce first. Add tests. Measure observer effects.</li><li>Post durable results to GitHub, -hackers, or CommitFest.</li></ol></div><div class="terminal"><div class="terminal-head">~/postgres-hacking/README</div><div class="terminal-body"><p><span class="prompt">$</span> values</p><p>public evidence &gt; recollection</p><p>tests &gt; confidence</p><p>small patches &gt; grand plans</p><p>review is work</p><p><span class="prompt">$</span> status</p><p><span class="warn">7 open lines</span></p><p><span class="danger">blockers visible</span></p><p><span class="prompt">community online</span></p></div></div></div></section>
  <section class="section"><div class="shell"><div class="callout"><p><strong>Research note:</strong> generic-title sessions without descriptions remain deliberately unmapped unless a same-day artifact or another public source identifies the topic. We do not manufacture provenance.</p></div></div></section>
</Layout>
